author: Hypebeast (info@hypebeast.com)
title: There's a 23 Savage Now
text:
Late last year, 21 Savage was dissed by a Baton Rouge rapper calling himself 22 Savage . It's 2017 and it looks like the buffoonery is far from stopping -- enter 23 Savage. This time, instead of slamming the original 21, 23 turns against 22 with the TheHitBrainiac-produced track "Ain't No 22." While this could whole debacle could be dismissed as a petty unoriginal spoof, the video has racked up over 600,000 views in just two days and continues to rise in popularity. In actuality, 23 Savage is a YouTuber who goes by the name of TheDissRapper, a parody artist who already has over 130,000 subscribers as of today. Watch the visual above and stay tuned for more.
Read more at Hypebeast.com
